##############################################################
#
#  Setup
#
#

Context("Numeric");
#given
$V1= random(1, 5,1);# [m/s]
$h1=random(2,5,1);# [m]

#computation
$Ans= (0.5*998*9.81*1*($h1**2-1)-998*$h1*1*$V1**2*($h1/1-1))/1000;# (kN)


#set tolerance
Context()->flags->set(
tolerance=>.05,);

##############################################################
#
#  PGML 
#
#

BEGIN_PGML

[@ image("UBC-FLU-18-071.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

A flowing river [`(1)`] passes over an underwater wall as shown, leaving at a different velocity and height [`(2)`]. Ignore atmospheric pressure and assume hydrostatic pressure at [`(1)`] and [`(2)`]. What is the force [`F`] exerted on the obstacle by the river if [`V_1=[$V1]`] [`m/s`], [`h_1=[$h1]`] [`m`], [`h_2=1`] [`m`], and [`b=1`] [`m`] ([`b`] is the width of the river into the screen).  
Neglect friction at the bottom of the river.   

[`F=`] [____]{"$Ans"} [`kN`]

END_PGML

